Jason Consoli, Fantasy sixth man The draft order Two-quarterback leagues are a bit of a different beast than standard fantasy football leagues. In fact, because of the late-round quarterback strategy, most analyst rankings don't account for these formats. Consider the pool of quarterbacks much slimmer when you can start two of them. Throw in a point per reception, and you have a draft that might be like no other. Not content with one-stop shopping come fantasy draft time? Eager to see what the wider fantasy football community has to say? You've come to the right place. Eleven top fantasy football analysts recently came together for a mock draft for a two-quarterback, PPR league that rewards four points per passing touchdown instead of six.
